Title: Series: Twelve Facsimile Etchings from very rare Originals by Rembrandt Van Ryn
Description: The flight into Egypt, a sketch; a man (Joseph) walking to left with stick, seen from behind, holding a donkey on a lead at right; arch-shaped plate; copy in same direction after Rembrandt. 1824 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: William James Smith
Curator's comments: This is one from a set of twelve, for comment see 1877,0811.1060. For the original etching by Rembrandt and comment see F,5.118.
Bibliographic references: New Hollstein (Dutch & Flemish) / The New Hollstein: Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts 1450-1700 (4) (Rembrandt; copy a)
Hind 1923 / A Catalogue of Rembrandt's Etchings; chronologically arranged and completely illustrated (17) (copy undescribed)
White & Boon 1969 / Rembrandt's Etchings: An Illustrated Critical Catalogue (54) (copy 1)
